      passage: `To evaluate their ideas about environmental conditions in the Pliocene epoch, paleontologists must turn to ______ evidence. Only material objects&mdash;such as the fossil remains of the individual known as AL 200-1, discovered in Ethiopia in 1975&mdash;can show whether a particular idea about the Pliocene is defensible.`,
